parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mount can cause the engine to shift, leading to loss of control, accidents, or fires.
symptoms: The engine and transmission shift to the right
making it difficult or impossible to shift gears
and the vehicle may experience fires or engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinge can cause the door to fall off, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The door becomes difficult to close
the door falls off
or the door hinge breaks
causing the door to separate from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the floor pan can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Rusting of the floor pan
corrosion of the frame member
and water leaks from the air conditioning system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mounts can cause the engine to shift, leading to damage to the fan, radiator, and other components, which can result in loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine mounts break
the engine shifts
the fan hits the radiator
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the engine drops
the motor mounts shear off
the fan blade hits the fan shroud
the engine rises 10-12 inches when pressing the accelerator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The crankshaft position sensor burns out
the engine stalls
the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The exhaust manifold cracks
the vehicle stalls
the exhaust fuel leaks inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle becomes dislodged
the seatbelt does not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil change gauge can cause the engine to seize or fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil change gauge is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radiator has rust around it
the vehicle has coolant leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake rotors rust or corrode
causing the vehicle to vibrate or pulsate when braking
leading to poor braking ability
grinding or thumping sounds when applying the brakes
and in some cases
the rotors may separate or crack
causing the vehicle to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
and in some cases
the vehicle may crash or be involved in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to properly repair or replace the brake rotors during the recall process can lead to continued brake problems, accidents, or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake rotors are not properly replaced or repaired during the recall process
leading to continued brake problems
including rust or corrosion
vibration or pulsation when braking
and poor braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
often when shifting gears or applying brakes
resulting in loss of control
accidents
and injuries.
